 Business of Fashion





Business of FashionMacy’s Expertise in Business



The Business of Fashion
Macy’s has a long history of innovation in business. We’re continually looking for new ways to delight the customer, deliver value and build sales and profits, and we've long been recognized for our commitment to fostering the growth and development of our vendor resources, including owned enterprises.





Macy’s, Inc. is a premier omnichannel retailer with iconic brands that serve customers through outstanding stores, dynamic online sites and mobile apps. Both Macy’s and Bloomingdale’s are known worldwide, and each has its own unique identity and customer focus. Bluemercury is widely recognized as the nation’s largest and fastest-growing luxury beauty products and spa retail chain.
Macy’s, Inc., with corporate offices in Cincinnati and New York, is one of the nation’s premier retailers, with fiscal 2015 sales of $27.1 billion. The company operates about 870 stores in 45 states, the District of Columbia, Guam and Puerto Rico under the names Macy’s, Macy’s Backstage, Bloomingdale’s and Bloomindale’s Outlet and Bluemercury, as well as the macys.com, bloomingdales.com and bluemercury.com websites.
We clearly recognize that the customer is paramount and that all its actions and omnichannel strategies must be directed toward providing a personalized merchandise offering and shopping experience.
Macy’s has a long history of innovation in business; in fact, we were named one of the World’s Top 10 Innovative Retailers by Fast Company Magazine. We’re continually looking for new ways to delight the customer, deliver value and build sales and profits, and we’ve long been recognized for our commitment to fostering the growth and development of our vendor resources, including minority- and women- owned enterprises.
To help achieve our goal of expanding vendor diversity in our retail stores and offer our customers the best assortment, we offer The Workshop at Macy’s. This comprehensive retail vendor development program includes an intensive four-and-a-half-day workshop designed to give select high potential minority- and women-owned companies the tools to better succeed and sustain growth in the retail industry.
To apply for the program often called “life-changing” by participants, review the eligibility requirements and  submit your application before the deadline. And the program is free. Yes, you read that right. To learn more, see the program overview and read what past participants have to say. You can also explore success stories of past Workshop participants and learn more about the impact it’s had on their businesses through a series of video interviews.  Find out what applying for the Workshop at Macy’s could do for your business.
We’re accepting applications until 11:59 PM EST on January 29, 2017.  Apply now!










