Product Development

       Product Development interns are given the unique opportunity of helping to fashion and advance a specific new product line, gaining invaluable insight into the production cycle in the process. 

  Working as an integral part of your team, you’ll learn all aspects of product development, from concept to production. Interns also have regular interaction with overseas offices, the global vendor community and merchant partners to develop strategy for sourcing Private Brands. Plus, along the way you’ll sharpen your presentation, communications and time management skills.























A Day in the Life
Product Development is at the forefront of innovation—in one of the most innovative companies in the retail industry. We don’t have boring roles. And we don’t want them. Check out how a day might go for you as a member of the Product Development team.

Learn More






Locations and Start DatesOur Product Development Summer Internship is offered at our corporate offices in New York City. The program starts in June.TrainingProfessional development begins on day one with a combination of structured classes and in-office experiences. During the 8-week paid internship you will work with business partners on your assigned team as well as other key executives across the organization. The structured all-intern sessions will give you an opportunity to network with 100+ headquarter interns while learning about retail innovation and Macy’s big-picture business strategies. You will complete a collaborative group project and present your recommendation to key leaders. At the end of the eight weeks, you will receive performance feedback from your assigned team and leave the internship program with a greater understanding of how to analyze and drive sales.ImpactAs a product development intern, you will have the opportunity to learn and make an impact from the start. Working with a team of product experts, you will develop your business knowledge in areas such as: sourcing, negotiation, and production. You will learn the importance of collaboration across teams to drive sales and profitability. At the end of the eight weeks you will leave the internship program with a greater understanding of the Product Life Cycle from concept to customer.Career GrowthThis is your opportunity to join an organization dedicated to developing its employees and providing executives with the necessary tools to be successful. In addition to learning about Macy’s Private Brands, the internship will provide you with exposure to Macy’s total business model and determine where your skill sets are best matched. Interns who demonstrate the understanding and ability to deliver results within the organization will be eligible for a full-time position in our Executive Development Program post-graduation.

What is a Private Brand?


            Private Brands are product lines that are manufactured  exclusively for a 
            specific retailer.  Macy's has an awesome Private Brands team that works 
            to identify new product opportunities and ensure we offer a wide range of 
            private label products that are trend right and available to our stores and 
            online customers at the right price, place, and time they need them.
         


Product Development






                Product Development Executives work closely with our overseas and domestic partners to manage the total production process - from designing to sourcing to costing - of our Private Label goods.  Product Development executives possess a strong balance of trend awareness and business savvy to adapt to our consumer's changing needs.

                






        Product Development Executive Development Program
        



            During this 18-month layered development program, you’ll learn the fundamentals 
            of conceptualizing, designing, sourcing, producing, selling and marketing our
             highly successful Private Brands; your training will supplement hands-on
             experience with multiple and varied training opportunities.
        


        Assistant / Specialist

        



           Assistants learn the operational components of running a successful business while receiving significant exposure and development. This is a developmental role that prepares you for an Associate role.

        


        Associate:

        



           Associates are given direct responsibility for a particular category within their team's total product line. In many cases, Associates will assume the responsibility of managing and training the Assistants.  This is a developmental role that prepares you for a Product Manager role.

        


        Product Manager

        



            Product Managers are responsible for the sales and profitability of a total category of business through strategy development and execution, as well as leading and developing their team of assistants/associates.  
        


        Product Director

        



            Director level is responsible for providing leadership driving and managing the Private Brand business and direct MMG Product Teams in the line development. 

        


        Vice President

        



            Vice Presidents are responsible for directing the strategy and execution for a designated division of business.

        


        Executive Vice President

        



           In these senior level positions, executives direct the financial objectives, product development, and strategy for multiple divisions of business.

        


        Chief Private Brands Officer

        


QualificationsMacy’s is looking for the future leaders of our organization and individuals dedicated to their development. To be
eligible for the Product Development Internship, you should be in your junior year, on your way to earning a bachelor’s degree from an accredited university. A minimum cumulative 3.0 GPA is preferred. All majors will be considered for this opportunity.
 A few of the qualities that would make an ideal candidate include: demonstrated leadership skills, assertiveness, intellectual curiosity, and strong business acumen with the ability to analyze data and draw conclusions.






Macy’s Snapshots
Product Development

            The people are real. The places are real. The photos are real. 
            Making this your perfect opportunity to go behind the scenes and get a genuine glimpse of Macy's Product Development inner workings.
        

